
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `brltty-tune` baraye tanzeemat va ayar-e kardan-e Brltty (software-e namayesh-e khat-e barjaste) estefade mishavad. Ba estefade az in dastoor, mitavanid namayeshgar-e khat-e barjaste va khosusiate aan ra motabegh ba niaz-e khod tanzeem konid.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `--help`        --> ❓ Namayesh-e rahnama va etela'at-e bishtar dar mored-e dastoor.
    🔹 `--list-drivers` --> 📝 List-e driver-haye dastras baraye namayeshgar-e khat-e barjaste ra namayesh midahad.
    🔹 `--driver <driver>`  --> ⚙️ Entkhab-e driver-e makhsoos baraye namayeshgar. Bayad az list-e driver-ha entkhab shavad.
    🔹 `--port <port>`  --> 📍 Moshakhas kardane port-e serial ya USB ke namayeshgar be aan vasl ast.
    🔹 `--baud <baud>`  --> 📶 Tanzeem-e sor'at-e baud baraye ertebat-e serial (dar surati ke estefade shavad).
    🔹 `--config <file>` --> 📄 Load-e config az yek file makhsoos.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ sudo brltty-tune --list-drivers

    🔹 Namayesh list-e driver-haye dastras. Shoma bayad `sudo` estefade konid chon tanzeemat bar rooye system asar migozarad.

    $ sudo brltty-tune --driver alva --port /dev/ttyUSB0

    🔹 Tanzeem-e Brltty baraye estefade az driver-e "alva" ba estefade az port-e USB be onvane `/dev/ttyUSB0`.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ brltty-tune --help

    🔹 In dastoor rahnama-ye kameli az gozine-ha va estefade-ye `brltty-tune` ra namayesh midahad.  Baraaye fahmidane behtare dastoor va parametrhaye an kheili mofid ast.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `brltty-tune` command is used to configure and tune Brltty (a braille display software).  It allows you to customize your braille display and its features according to your needs.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `--help`        --> ❓ Display help information and more details about the command.
    🔹 `--list-drivers` --> 📝 Show a list of available drivers for braille displays.
    🔹 `--driver <driver>`  --> ⚙️ Select a specific driver for the display.  Must be chosen from the available list.
    🔹 `--port <port>`  --> 📍 Specify the serial or USB port to which the display is connected.
    🔹 `--baud <baud>`  --> 📶 Set the baud rate for serial communication (if applicable).
    🔹 `--config <file>` --> 📄 Load configuration from a specified file.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ sudo brltty-tune --list-drivers

    🔹 Display the list of available drivers. You need to use `sudo` because configuration changes affect the system.

    $ sudo brltty-tune --driver alva --port /dev/ttyUSB0

    🔹 Configure Brltty to use the "alva" driver with the USB port at `/dev/ttyUSB0`.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ brltty-tune --help

    🔹 This command will show you a complete guide with all available options and usages of `brltty-tune`. This is very helpful for understanding the command and its parameters.
